{
  "texts": [
    "As worldsheet fields, β(z) and γ(z) are commuting holomorphic fields of weight 1 and 0 respectively and ∂Φ(z) is a free boson of weight 1.",
    "In order to reproduce the correct current algebra of sl(2, R) 1, these fields must have the nontrivial OPEsβ(z)γ(w) ∼ 1 (z -w), ∂Φ(z)∂Φ(w) ∼ 1 2(z -w) 2.",
    "( 2.16)There is a normal ordering correction to J -, discussed further below and given by [4]J -= 2γdΦ -dγ -Bγ 2.Such a realisation of the current algebra has been motivated by the Wakimoto representation of sl(2, R) 1, first studied in [41], but has since been applied to string theory on AdS 3 in order to provide a semi-classical interpretation to the theory (for example, [4,15,25]).It has also been used to construct the boundary CFT [5].",
    "The real utility of this (free field) Wakimoto representation is that the (quasi-)primary fields describing it have natural spacetime interpretations.",
    "How can this free field representation be reconciled with the (interacting) non-linear sigma model on AdS 3?"
  ]
}